reviews.text: Day trip to Goleta for Disc Golf and hiking at Gaviota, landed us here for food afterward. Unfortunately, missed breakfast but got pizza and salad. The food was very good, but not great. We heard breakfast is what people come here for, so why not breakfast all day? Anyway, still highly recommended. We‚Äôll be back another time for breakfast.

I attended an event on the patio designed to facilitate communication between the neighborhood and the new City Council member, Jennifer Smith. Between speakers and Q&A, I poked my head in to see the menu and observe the hardworking staff. This place clearly serves as a hub for those in the surrounding neighborhoods. I so admire that they provided a space for traffic engineers, planners, cops, and politicians to engage with the public. It was fun to watch staff members darting through the crowd to deliver delicious-looking plates to customers in the tavern a few doors down. I greatly enjoyed a few cups of coffee and chatting with officials and residents of this great community. Thank you, Home Plate for serving up some delicious democracy on a Saturday morning. My family will be by soon to dine with you.

Wonderful locally owned small business. Best wagyu burger in town! Every time I visit, the staff is warm and welcoming. They serve a wide variety of delicious food. Great location catering to the residents near the El Encanto Heighs neighborhood. They also own the sports bar next door. Highly recommend!
Ready for a great breakfast? You‚Äôre in for a treat. The chilaquiles are the best I‚Äôve ever had! They know what o er medium means, generous portions. Good coffee and fantastic prices!

Home Plate Grill has well cooked food, indoor and outdoor seats, and good service overall. Biggest thing is to use the condiments on the table (salt/pepper/sugar) to adjust.

If I were to come back, I'd order the "Chicken Fried Pork Chop" and the "French Toast Sammy", both of those could hold on their own without extra seasoning.

detailedReviews.text: We found Home Plate Grill online and decided to give it a try, we are so glad we did!  The atmosphere is nothing fancy, but the food is phenomenal!  My husband and I had breakfast; Chilli Verde Rancheros and Gaucho Burrito (but as a bowl), they were so good!  The spicy Bloody Mary's were amazing, too.  The next day we brought our son (who's at UCSB) to experience the deliciousness.  He loved it too, obviously.  A hidden gem!

detailedReviews.text: We absolutely love Home Plate Grill. There are few other restaurants that feel more authentic to Goleta. detailedReviews.text: Stopped here for breakfast on my road trip from Toronto to LA in July. Absolutely amazing food for a steal! The servers were attentive and helpful. Definitely recommend this place to anyone passing by.

detailedReviews.author: Michelle Quinn
detailedReviews.text: I remember when they first opened, it was a great place to go have lunch or dinner with you family or friends. Is since gone way down hill. I have been 3 times in the last two months hoping that maybe it was just a bad day for them but the food has continually gotten worse. Today, I found wilty brown lettuce on my sandwicheand what tasted like a "going bad" avocado. I am all for supporting small businesses but these guys need to change something. I'm not sure if it changed owners or what, but I won't be back until, at least the lettuce is crisp again.

detailedReviews.author: Dean Wittke
detailedReviews.text:
Just found this place by accident.  We were going to have breakfast in Solvang, but the lines were extremely long and it was raining, so went on.

This is no doubt the best breakfast place I have eaten at in the last year or so, maybe more.  I love funky local places, not sterile chains, and this fits the bill.

The prices are great, the service is excellent, and the food is outstanding.
